title: Misleading graphs for RNN network Dataset 2
body: The graphs for the accuracy and loss rates for RNN results for dataset 2 do not have the same scale as the CNN and HAN results. The non-matching scaling factor causes the RNN graphs to indicate higher accuracy than they should when visually compared with the CNN and HAN graphs.

title: Cheetah Issue:
body:
Hi, I am trying to use the cheetah streaming with microphone option.
I am trying to use the cheetah.process, and the requested format is:

:param pcm: A frame of audio samples. The number of samples per frame can be attained by calling
        `.frame_length`. The incoming audio needs to have a sample rate equal to `.sample_rate` and be 16-bit
        linearly-encoded. Furthermore, Cheetah operates on single-channel audio.

how can I live stream an audio that will answer the requirements?
I am using python, and I tried PyAudio but was not successful.
I will appreciate help and examples from someone who managed to do so.

Thanks!

title: Acoustic Echo Cancellation
body:
**Is your feature request related to a problem? Please describe.**
If I am playing back synthesized voice and I am also listening to the microphone with Cheetah, I will get the synth content transcribed by cheetah.  I have been looking into Acoustic Echo Cancellation to get around this.  Before I implement something with say SpeexDSP I thought it is worth asking if there is a feature from Picovoice that will accomplish this?

**Describe the solution you'd like**
If Cheetah has integrated AEC that would be ideal.  Alternatively there is a filter or something like it that I could insert into the TargetDataLine (I am using Java API) before passing to Cheetah.

**Describe alternatives you've considered**
I've considered implementing my own AEC with SpeexDSP.  It is a C library so I would need to understand Speex itself, C and JNI to do this.  It is possible, but if it is an already solved problem then I would prefer to go that route..

**Additional context**
If there is another alternative I would be interested to learn of it.  I know that Android platform has Java version of AEC but I am not sure if that will work in generic Java environment.  I also understand ByteDance has a solution however it is proprietary and I am not sure how to evaluate..

title: Cheetah + Eagle
body:
**Is your feature request related to a problem? Please describe.**
I want to identify people speaking in live transcriptions. However, I can't find a way to correlate the output of Eagle (https://picovoice.ai/docs/api/eagle-web/) with the output of Cheetah because Cheetah is async (no correlation of output to the input frame), whereas Eagle gives one-to-one results correlated with input audio frame.

**Describe the solution you'd like**
Any way of making Eagle work with Cheetah.

Perhaps timestamps in Cheetah output so I can correlate the results myself, or direct integration of Eagle into Cheetah. Or at minimum, a specific awaitable sync API that I can use to process an audio frame, like Eagle has:

```
async function process(pcm: Int16Array): Promise<number[]>
```

Though for Cheetah, it could be:
```
async function process(pcm: Int16Array): Promise<string>
```

Even just THAT would be enough...can we get an async `process` call?

**Describe alternatives you've considered**
`whisper.cpp` 

**Additional context**
N/A

title: Cheetah Issue: Stack overflow crash in Cheetah during processing
body:
I have been integrating and evaluating Cheetah in a MacOS desktop application (Cheetah C library, arm64) and have been experiencing this issue, which is blocker for further development. I have been unable to debug this much further without understanding what could cause this behaviour inside the cheetah library.

### Expected behaviour

Transcription should be output

### Actual behaviour

App crashes with very large backtrace inside cheetah library

### Steps to reproduce the behaviour

Run the transcription for some time (10-15 minutes) eventually app will crash after working correctly during that time.

MacOS 13.0.1
Cheetah C library (latest version)
Target is MacOS

As far as I can tell, the buffer passed to pv_cheetah_process is valid, has content, and is accessible. App crashes with EXC_BAD_ACCESS and appears to be a stack overflow type crash.

The app and transcription works perfectly fine for some time before this happens. The crash consistently occurs after around 10 minutes runtime.

I am using AVAudioEngine to tap an input microphone. The buffer provided is converted and then fed into picovoice/cheetah.

### Backtrace

v10.2.6

Fix for memory leak on Listeners

The listener was not being removed on response and just error but new handlers were being added causing a memory leak.

line 220 in src/index.ts was modified to remove the listener on response also 

			if (this.cache instanceof Keyv) {
				const cachek = this.cache;
				cachek.once('error', errorHandler);
				ee.on('error', () => cachek.removeListener('error', errorHandler));

title: Error when attempting to provide model argument to web binding
body:
Make sure you have read the documentation, and have put forth a reasonable effort to find an existing answer.

### Expected behaviour

When creating an instance of the Cheetah engine with React in an attempt to use cheetah for  web, no methods I've tried are able to read the model file. 

### Actual behaviour

I receive the message
```The provided model doesn't contain a valid publicPath or base64 value``` 

### Steps to reproduce the behaviour

I try to create an instance of cheetah like so:

```
cheetah = await Cheetah.create(
        accessKey,
        cheetahTranscriptionCallback,
        './cheetah_model.pv'
      )

```
I've also tried importing the file (`import * as cheetahModel from './cheetah_model.pv`),  using Buffer to do base64 encoding and passing the result of that in, nothing works. What am i doing incorreclty here?

title: Bump bumpalo from 3.10.0 to 3.12.0 in /demo/rust/micdemo
body:
Bumps [bumpalo](https://github.com/fitzgen/bumpalo) from 3.10.0 to 3.12.0.
Changelog

Sourced from bumpalo's changelog.

3.12.0

Released 2023-01-17.

Added

  • Added the bumpalo::boxed::Box::bump and bumpalo::collections::String::bump getters to get the underlying Bump that a string or box was allocated into.

Changed

  • Some uses of Box that MIRI did not previously consider as UB are now reported as UB, and bumpalo's internals have been adjusted to avoid the new UB.

3.11.1

Released 2022-10-18.

Security

  • Fixed a bug where when std::vec::IntoIter was ported to bumpalo::collections::vec::IntoIter, it didn't get its underlying Bump's lifetime threaded through. This meant that rustc was not checking the borrows for bumpalo::collections::IntoIter and this could result in use-after-free bugs.

3.11.0

Released 2022-08-17.

Added

  • Added support for per-Bump allocation limits. These are enforced only in the slow path when allocating new chunks in the Bump, not in the bump allocation hot path, and therefore impose near zero overhead.
  • Added the bumpalo::boxed::Box::into_inner method.

Changed

  • Updated to Rust 2021 edition.
  • The minimum supported Rust version (MSRV) is now 1.56.0.

title: Absolute path for model file - Expo/React Native
body:
**Is your feature request related to a problem? Please describe.**
I'm attempting to use Picovoice-cheetah with an existing Expo react native application. Unfortunately, expo does not have an easy way to bundle the file into the application's asset directory for android, instead opting for it's own [asset management lib](https://docs.expo.dev/versions/latest/sdk/asset/). AFIK the Cheetah.create method is relative to the /asset/ path only.

**Describe the solution you'd like**
I'd like to simply provide an absolute path to the file system. I.e.: 
`file:///data/user/0/app/cache/ExponentAsset-4e3f888fc8475f69fd5fa32f1ad5216a.pv`

**Describe alternatives you've considered**
I'm not going to eject my app for this. 

**Additional context**
The model is fairly large, supporting this feature would also allow the model to be shipped independently of the app reducing bundle sizes.

title: Flutter - Android app crashes after initiating Cheetah voice detection
body:
I have built an application in Flutter, which uses Cheetah voice recognition.
While I run the release of my app on my phone via Android Studio and start the Cheetah voice recognition, the app crashes.

In my pubspec.yaml I have following dependencies:
  flutter_voice_processor: ^1.0.6
  cheetah_flutter: ^1.0.0

title: Recognizing Polish language in Cheetah speech-to-text
body:
Hi Picovoice team!

I am working on my Computer Science Master's Thesis, which is a mobile application for tracking the progress of your goals using the voice interface. I will be performing studies, which will compare user engagement with and without user interface to determine if voice control is something that increases the productivity and engagement of users.

I have searched through available solutions for Flutter and there is no other voice recognition solution as good as Picovoice! üòÑ 
In terms of API, reliability, and latency it is unmatched.

MVP is aimed primarily at the Polish market, which leads to my question: how can support for the Polish language be added?
Currently, the app has the most emphasis on continuous voice-to-text, which is why I am asking about Cheetah.

Hope to hear from you.

Best,
Dastin  Sandura

title: Bump react-native from 0.63.3 to 0.64.1 in /demo/react-native
body:
Bumps [react-native](https://github.com/facebook/react-native) from 0.63.3 to 0.64.1.
Release notes

Sourced from react-native's releases.

v0.64.1

This patch release is specifically targetted towards fixing iOS build problems in Xcode 12.5. If it doesn't help, please refer to this issue.

Aside from bumping your version from 0.64.0 to 0.64.1, please check your podfile.lock and make sure that Flipper is on 0.75 or higher, and Flipper-Folly is 2.5.3 or higher; if not, add this line to your podfile (or modify it if you already had it):

use_flipper!('Flipper' => '0.75.1', 'Flipper-Folly' => '2.5.3', 'Flipper-RSocket' => '1.3.1')

After which, do all the classic necessary cleans (node_modules, caches, pod folders, etc)(react-native-clean-project is your ally) then do yarn install and a pod install --repo-update (if pod install fails on an error about a Flipper package, just remove the relevant lines from the podfile.lock and run the pod install again).

The only other commit picked & released along the Xcode 12.5 fixes is:

  • Update validateBaseUrl to use latest regex (commit) which fixes CVE-2020-1920, GHSL-2020-293.

You can participate in the conversation on the status of this release at this issue.

To help you upgrade to this version, you can use the upgrade helper ‚öõÔ∏è

You can find the whole changelog history over at react-native-releases.

v0.64.0

0.64 stable is here üéâ

Thanks to everyone who contributed and helped to get this together, everyone worked really hard and we hope you are as excited as we are ü§ó

Some of the most important highlights of this version:

  • Hermes opt-in on iOS
  • Inline Requires enabled by default
  • React 17

Among many others - please refer to the blog post for more details.

You can participate in the conversation on the status of this release at this issue.

You can upgrade to this version using the upgrade helper webtool ‚öõÔ∏è And if you are having trouble, please refer to the new Upgrade Support repository by our awesome community.

... (truncated)

Changelog

Sourced from react-native's changelog.

v0.64.1

Fixed

iOS specific

  • Fixes to ensure Xcode 12.5 builds (cf8a364767, 1c4ac48a55 and 76f45d35e7 by @‚Äãkelset)

Security

  • Update validateBaseUrl to use latest regex (33ef82ce6d by @‚ÄãFBNeal)

v0.64.0

Breaking

  • Enable inlineRequires by default in new projects' metro.config.js. Gives a performance benefit but slightly different JS execution order (959365a902 by @‚ÄãGantMan)
  • Minimum supported Node version changed to 12 (4b92e2e53d by @‚Äãsafaiyeh)
  • Remove deprecated CameraRoll API (deprecated in 0.61) (824d3a9770 by @‚Äãseanyusa)
  • Remove deprecated CheckBox component (deprecated in 0.60) (dff17effe5 by @‚Äãpoteto)
  • Removed DEPRECATED_sendUpdatedChildFrames prop from ScrollView component (deprecated in 0.47) (345d0c1abb by @‚ÄãZHUANGPP)
  • On Image, onLoad event objects' source.url is now renamed to source.uri. (74ab8f6e5a by @‚Äãyungsters)

Android specific

  • Remove support of Android API levels 16 through 20. The new minSDK version will be 21+ moving forward. (973198667d, 25a40cbc61, f829722b54, b133427778, 9b34aa261c, and 79d0a7d711 by @‚Äãmdvacca; 49f10fd2e5 and a17ff44adc by @‚ÄãJoshuaGross; dd4298a377 by @‚Äãsafaiyeh)
  • Fix ReadableArray null annotations. Possibly breaking change for Kotlin apps. (d76556543f by @‚Äãdulmandakh)
  • On Image, onLoad and onError event objects will no longer have an extra uri property. (74ab8f6e5a by @‚Äãyungsters)
  • Deletes the method PlayTouchSound method from UIManagerModule, this method was moved to the SoundManagerModule class. (d0c4c5eaf9 by @‚Äãmdvacca)

iOS specific

  • Remove calculateChildFrames from RCTScrollView (62aa84a325 by @‚ÄãPeteTheHeat)

Deprecated

Android specific

  • Deprecated method UIManagerModule.getUIImplementation. This method will not be part of the new architecture of React Native. (fe79abb32c by @‚Äãmdvacca)

Added

  • Adds the Hermes runtime bytecode version number to the JS bundle requestURL. This allows Metro with Bytecode to work with prebuilt binaries. (34c405462f)
  • TextInput now supports onPressIn and onPressOut. (b7b0e23202 by @‚Äãyungsters)
  • Allow setting a custom performance logger in XMLHttpRequest (57b10f759e by @‚Äãrubennorte)
  • Add mock for DevSettings to jest preset (a50f736bb6 by @‚ÄãMarcoScabbiolo)
  • Added Inspector overlay support for Pressable (8ac467c51b by @‚Äãyungsters)
  • Introduce NativeModulePerfLogger (0486640571 by @‚ÄãRSNara)
  • Add default titlePlaceholder in template configuration. (8ffa180d80 by @‚ÄãEsemesek)
  • Modified renderApplication to forward initialProps to WrapperComponent (4f5a092bf6 by @‚Äãrubennorte)

title: Cheetah licensing
body:
I developed a speech-to-text application for sharing the transcript to many concurrently.
See [https://github.com/zSeriesGuy/SpeakReader](https://github.com/zSeriesGuy/SpeakReader)

It takes microphone or line-in input to the server and sends the transcription to any number of connected web browsers.
It currently uses the Google Speech-to-text cloud platform. But I intend to extend it to support other speech-to-text engines.
I found Cheetah to be an interesting option.

How does the licensing work? My project requires the user of the app to set up their own license with Google Cloud. If I were to incorporate Cheetah as a selectable stt engine option, how would someone obtain a license file?

title: Real-time processing demo (Python), and slight refactoring of cheetah_demo.py
body:
`cheetah_demo.py` script is refactored to use functions, some of which are used in the new demo.

The new demo - `realtime_demo.py` - uses `PyAudio` and processes input from an audio input device in real time, and transcribes after it is interrupted by the user (i.e. receives SIGINT) with ctrl+C. Tested on Ubuntu, x86 machine.
